commText: Philip Salt and Narine are at the crease. Philip Salt is on strike. Tushar Deshpande will open the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Philip Salt, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Tushar Deshpande to Philip Salt, out Caught by Jadeja!! Tushar Deshpande strikes on the first ball! Back of a length outside off, Philip Salt throws his hands at it, carves it towards backward point where Jadeja takes a sharp catch. Philip Salt departs without troubling the scorers. Philip Salt c Jadeja b Tushar Deshpande 0(1)
Angkrish Raghuvanshi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Tushar Deshpande to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, back of a length around off, Angkrish Raghuvanshi steers it to point
Tushar Deshpande to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, on a length around off, Angkrish Raghuvanshi plays it late, steering it to third man for a single
Tushar Deshpande to Narine, no run, short of a length around middle and leg, pulled to mid-on by the batter
Tushar Deshpande to Narine, no run, proving to be a fantastic start by Tushar Deshpande. Back of a length around leg, cramped for room, Narine gets beaten on the inside edge
Tushar Deshpande to Narine, no run, just a single from the first over. Superb start by Tushar Deshpande. Short and wide outside off, Narine tries to reach out for it, connects thin air
Mustafizur has a wide slip in place..
Mustafizur Rahman, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mustafizur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, that kept slightly low outside off, Angkrish Raghuvanshi plays it late, steering it to third man for one
Mustafizur to Narine, 1 run, short of a length around middle and leg, Narine swings across the line, mistimes it towards mid-on
Mustafizur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, short of a length around off, Angkrish Raghuvanshi steers it to point off his back foot

Mustafizur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, first positive shot of the match. Angkrish Raghuvanshi shimmies down the wicket and thumps the length delivery over wide mid-off with authority, gets the first boundary of the match
Mustafizur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, lovely delivery, typical Mustafiz as the back of a length delivery shapes away slightly, Angkrish Raghuvanshi has a feeble poke, almost nicks it behind
Mustafizur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, the slower delivery outside off, a cutter by Mustafizur at 116 clicks, Angkrish Raghuvanshi shuffles across, he swings and misses
Tushar Deshpande to Narine, leg byes, FOUR, some bonus runs for KKR. Short of a length around leg, Narine was cramped for room as the ball clips the thigh pad and races away to the fine leg boundary

Tushar Deshpande to Narine, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries. First one was a leg bye, but this was off the bat. He tried to whip it away, ended up getting an inside edge through backward square leg for four more
Tushar Deshpande to Narine, no run, short of a length outside off, Narine has a swing and a miss
The physio walks out to the middle. Narine's struggling with his left forehand or shoulder I think.. Not really sure what exactly the issue is..
CSK bowler to take a wicket on the first ball of the match Lakshmipathy Balaji vs DC, 2009 Deepak Chahar vs SRH, 2018 Tushar Deshpande v KKR, today*
KKR batters to be dismissed on the first ball of a match B McCullum vs RCB, 2009 Manoj Tiwary vs Deccan, 2010 J Kallis vs DC, 2014 J Denly vs DC, 2019 Phil Salt vs CSK, 2024*
Tushar Deshpande to Narine, FOUR, definitely some trouble with his shoulder. Was a length delivery and Narine thumped it over mid-off, immediately showed some discomfort confirm the replays..
Tushar Deshpande to Narine, wide, fires this down the leg-side, it's a wide ball

Tushar Deshpande to Narine, SIX, doesn't matter if he's injured, he'll do what he has been doing. Short of a length around leg, Narine flicks it over deep backward square leg and just manages to clear Mitchell's leap near the boundary
Tushar Deshpande to Narine, no run, back of a length around leg, Narine looks to nudge it away, gets hit on the pads. 19 runs from that over..
Shardul Thakur, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, easy pickings! Loose delivery down the leg-side, Angkrish Raghuvanshi glances away to the fine leg fence for four more. KKR's innings slowly getting back on track after that early dismissal
Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, short of a length around off, Angkrish Raghuvanshi slices it towards point
Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, back of a length around middle and leg, clipped through square leg for a single

Thakur to Narine, FOUR, drilled down the ground! Thakur goes full on off and Narine drives it crisply past the non-striker. Still struggling with that shoulder, quite evident once he's going hard after the bowler
Thakur to Narine, 1 run, yorker length delivery on off, Narine squeezes it into the off-side for one
Thakur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, quick run to end the over. On a length around middle and leg, nudged to mid-wicket by Angkrish Raghuvanshi as he scampers across
Last five opening stands for KKR vs CSK at Chepauk 1 (2) 19 (9) 6 (6) 4 (6) 0 (1) - today
Maheesh Theekshana, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Theekshana to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, eased towards cover-point by Angkrish Raghuvanshi

Theekshana to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, SIX, first maximum for Angkrish Raghuvanshi! A tossed up delivery by Theekshana, Angkrish Raghuvanshi stays put and launches it over the bowler's head for half-a-dozen. 81m maximum as Gaikwad wipes off the sweat on his forehead
Theekshana to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, flatter through the air on middle and leg, clipped through the leg-side for a single
Theekshana to Narine, no run, quicker through the air on leg, Narine works it to square leg with a closed bat face
Theekshana to Narine, no run, that kept low on leg, was slightly short as Narine swung across the line, got hit on the pads. Was clealy pitching outside leg

Theekshana to Narine, SIX, 50 up with a maximum! Just before this ball, the crowd was chanting 'CSK, CSK,' and Narine silences them with this thumping blow. Picks the bones out of the length delivery and sends it sailing over the long-on boundary. He's off to another fine start
Change of balls as the previous one got damaged I guess..
Mustafizur Rahman [1.0-0-6-0] is back into the attack

Mustafizur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, deft touch. This was full in length outside off and Angkrish Raghuvanshi reaches out for it, slices it through backward point for four runs. No one in the deep to cut it down
Mustafizur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, advances down the wicket and slices the back of a length delivery to backward point
Mustafizur to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Angkrish Raghuvanshi rocks back and punches it through point for one
A few changes in the field as the bowler asks the fielder on the leg-side to move squarer
Mustafizur to Narine, no run, goes short around off, Narine sways away from its line
Mustafizur to Narine, no run, another well directed bouncer by Mustafizur, Narine ducks for cover
Mustafizur to Narine, wide, attempted slower one but slides it down the leg-side, it's a wide ball by the Fizz

Mustafizur to Narine, no run, short of a length around off, Narine slaps it back to Mustafizur. He collects it and mimes a throw at the batter, quite an economical over, just like his first one. Most expensive powerplay by CSK at Chepauk this season

Powerplay summary -- Salt falls first ball of the match -- Narine off to another fast start -- Deshpande's second over goes for 19 -- Shardul, Theekshana taken for runs in their first overs -- Raghuvanshi looking good in the middle again
Ravindra Jadeja, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Jadeja to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Jadeja to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, out Lbw!! Jadeja strikes on his first ball, just like Tushar Deshpande did earlier in the innings. A flatter delivery on middle and leg, Angkrish Raghuvanshi tries to be cheeky, goes for the reverse sweep and gets rapped on the pads. The bowler goes up in an appeal and up goes the umpire's finger as well. The young batsman walks back after playing a handy cameo. Doesn't bother of taking a review, because this looked out.. Angkrish Raghuvanshi lbw b Jadeja 24(18) [4s-3 6s-1]
Powerplay scores for KKR this IPL 3/43 vs SRH 0/85 vs RCB 1/88 vs DC 1/56 vs CSK*
Sunil Narine's batting in PP this IPL Inns: 4 Runs: 127 Balls: 63 one dismissal SR: 201.58 4s/6s: 11/11
Shreyas Iyer, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Jadeja to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, floated on off, Shreyas Iyer steers it through point for a single
Jadeja to Narine, wide, fires this well outside off, it's a wide ball
Jadeja to Narine, 1 run, fraction short on leg, Narine swipes it towards deep square leg on a few bounces
Jadeja to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, Jadeja goes full on off as Shreyas Iyer drives it to wide long-off for a single
Jadeja to Narine, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Jadeja to Narine, out Caught by Theekshana!! Jadeja strikes twice in his first over. Gets the wicket of the danger man - Sunil Narine. Width on offer outside off and Narine looks to take him on. Throws his hands at this widish delivery and miscues it towards wide long-off. Theekshana stationed in the deep takes a safe reverse cup and that's that from Narine with the bat. Didn't look comfortable since that shoulder niggle, but hopefully it's nothing serious. Narine c Theekshana b Jadeja 27(20) [4s-3 6s-2]
Narine vs Jadeja in IPL Runs: 15 Balls: 9 three dismissals Avg: 5.00
Venkatesh Iyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Jadeja to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, tad short on leg, Venky nudges it through backward square leg for a single
Maheesh Theekshana [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Theekshana to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, flatter delivery on middle and leg, nudged back to the bowler
Theekshana to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, quicker through the air on off, Venkatesh Iyer goes for a cut, gets an inside edge towards Dhoni
Theekshana to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, full and straight outside off, Venkatesh Iyer swings and misses
Theekshana to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, Venkatesh Iyer struggling against Theekshana. This was probably the carrom ball around off, Venkatesh gets an inside edge on to the pads
Theekshana to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, another dot ball. Pressure building on Venkatesh. This was floated on off and it spun away slightly to beat Venkatesh's outside edge

Theekshana to Venkatesh Iyer, 2 runs, tad short outside off, Venkatesh Iyer plays it late, cuts it past Jadeja at short third man. He chases it all the down to the boundary and flicks the ball inside play, keeps them down to two
Jadeja to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, tad short on middle and leg, Shreyas Iyer works it through backward square leg for a single
Jadeja to Venkatesh Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Jadeja to Venkatesh Iyer, out Caught by Mitchell!! Venkatesh Iyer's struggle comes to an end. Walks back after playing a rusty knock as Jadeja is on absolute fire. Goes short and quick around middle, Venkatesh Iyer pulls it towards mid-wicket where Mitchell completes a fine running catch to his right. That shall also be the strategic timeout.. Venkatesh Iyer c Mitchell b Jadeja 3(8)
Timeout! CSK on top and it's Jadeja who has taken three wickets to derail KKR's innings. They need a partnership to steady the ship..
Ramandeep Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Jadeja to Ramandeep Singh, 2 runs, they are losing wickets, but KKR are not changing their approach. This was wide outside off and Ramandeep Singh makes room to loft it over cover for a couple of runs

Jadeja to Ramandeep Singh, no run, eased into the off-side by Ramandeep Singh this time around
Jadeja to Ramandeep Singh, no run, tad quicker outside off, Ramandeep Singh chops it to backward point. Another fantastic over, just three runs and a wicket in it..

Ravindra to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, Ravindra goes full on off, Shreyas Iyer drives this along the carpet to long-off for a single
Ravindra to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, flatter delivery on off, Ramandeep Singh sweeps it through mid-wicket for a single
Ravindra to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, a lot slower through the air, Shreyas Iyer pushes it towards cover-point for one
Ravindra to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, tad short outside off, punched through the off-side for a single
Jadeja to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, fraction short on off, punched to wide long-off for a single

Ramandeep gets beaten as the ball zips through and finds the middle stump rattled. CSK spinners owning KKR batters in front of the Chepauk crowd. Ramandeep Singh b Theekshana 13(12) [6s-1]

21:16 Local Time, 15:46 GMT, 21:16 IST: What a comeback this from CSK. KKR were 50/1 after 5 overs and the pitch showed no signs of what was to come. But enter Jadeja and the game changed on its head. Three quick wickets and the pitch too changed dramatically. It aided the spinners and Mustafizur too resorted to bowling fast offspin at the end. The slower balls did not come on, made stroke-making extremely difficult and KKR just couldn't get to grips with the pitch. Batters came and went and no-one was able to get the big hits going. At one stage KKR even had Manish Pandey ready to come in as the impact sub. Shreyas Iyer nudged his way to 34 off 32 and it is advantage CSK at the moment. But KKR have two excellent spinners in Narine and Chakaravarthy and they will feel they can still make a match out of this. Back for the reply in 5 minutes...

Jadeja: He (Mustafizur) was very effective on this wicket, he bowled very good slower ones, he was amazing I think. When dew comes in the wicket changes here, it gets better for batting. There was slow turn, it's not a rank turner. The ball wasn't coming on to the bat nicely, just tried to target the stumps. If we play normal cricket, I think very easily chaseable on this wicket.
